pan class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">h</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">S</span>.<a href=\"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Sites/Sieves.html#CategoryTheory.Sieve.arrows\">arrows</a></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#LE.le\">≤</a> <span class=\"fn\">R</span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">trans</span> : <span class=\"fn\">∀ ⦃<span class=\"fn\">Y</span> : <span class=\"fn\">C</span>⦄ (<span class=\"fn\">f</span> : <span class=\"fn\">Y</span> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Combinatorics/Quiver/Basic.html#Quiver.Hom\">⟶</a> <span class=\"fn\">X</span>), <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Sites/IsSheafFor.html#CategoryTheory.Presieve.IsSheafFor\">IsSheafFor</a> <span class=\"fn\">P</span> <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Sites/Sieves.html#CategoryTheory.Sieve.pullback\">Sieve.pullback</a> <span class=\"fn\">f</span> <span class=\"fn\">S</span>)</span>.<a href=\"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Sites/Sieves.html#CategoryTheory.Sieve.arrows\">arrows</a></span></span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Sites/IsSheafFor.html#CategoryTheory.Presieve.IsSheafFor\">IsSheafFor</a> <span class=\"fn\">P</span> <span class=\"fn\">R</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"If `P` is a sheaf for every pullback of the sieve `S`, then `P` is a sheaf for any presieve which\ncontains `S`.\nThis is closely related to [Elephant] C2.1.6.\n","docLink":"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Sites/IsSheafFor.html#CategoryTheory.Presieve.isSheafFor_subsieve","kind":"theorem","line":734,"name":"CategoryTheory.Presieve.isSheafFor_subsieve","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/087469e24922b85cb737497c74556c7dacc01f22/Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Sites/IsSheafFor.lean#L734-L743"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>