Link":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/087469e24922b85cb737497c74556c7dacc01f22/Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Sites/IsSheafFor.lean#L508-L521"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Sites/IsSheafFor.html#CategoryTheory.Presieve.natTransEquivCompatibleFamily\"><span class=\"name\">CategoryTheory</span>.<span class=\"name\">Presieve</span>.<span class=\"name\">natTransEquivCompatibleFamily</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">C</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u₁}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Category/Basic.html#CategoryTheory.Category\">Category.{v₁, u₁}</a> <span class=\"fn\">C</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">X</span> : <span class=\"fn\">C</span>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">S</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Sites/Sieves.html#CategoryTheory.Sieve\">Sieve</a> <span class=\"fn\">X</span></span>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">P</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Functor/Basic.html#CategoryTheory.Functor\">Functor</a> <span class=\"fn\">C</span><a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Opposite.html#Opposite\">ᵒᵖ</a> <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">(Type</a> v₁)</span>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\">(<span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">S</span>.<a href=\"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Sites/Sieves.html#CategoryTheory.Sieve.functor\">functor</a></span> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Combinatorics/Quiver/Basic.html#Quiver.Hom\">⟶</a> <span class=\"fn\">P</span>) <a href=\"./Mathlib/Logic/Equiv/Defs.html#Equiv\">≃</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Subtype\">{</a> <span class=\"fn\">x</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Subtype\">:</a> <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Sites/IsSheafFor.html#CategoryTheory.Presieve.FamilyOfElements\">FamilyOfElements</a> <span class=\"fn\">P</span> <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">S</span>.<a href=\"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Sites/Sieves.html#CategoryTheory.Sieve.arrows\">arrows</a></span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Subtype\">//</a> <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">x</span>.<a href=\"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Sites/IsSheafFor.html#CategoryTheory.Presieve.FamilyOfElements.Compatible\">Compatible</a></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Subtype\">}</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"(Implementation). This is a (primarily internal) equivalence between natural transformations\nand compatible families.\n\nCf the discussion after Lemma 7.47.10 in <https://stacks.math.columbia.edu/tag/00YW>. See also\nthe proof of C2.1.4 of [Elephant], and the discussion in [MM92], Chapter III, Section 4.\n","docLink":"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Sites/IsSheafFor.html#CategoryTheory.Presieve.natTransEquivCompatibleFamily","kind":"def","line":480,"name":"CategoryTheory.Presieve.natTransEquivCompatibleFamily","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/087469e24922b85cb737497c74556c7dacc01f22/Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Sites/IsSheafFor.lean#L480-L506"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Sites/IsSheafFor.html#CategoryTheory.Presieve.YonedaSheafCondition\"><span class=\"name\">CategoryTheory</span>.<span class=\"name\">Presieve</span>.<span class=\"name\">YonedaSheafCondition</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">C</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u₁}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Category/Basic.html#CategoryTheory.Category\">Category.{v₁, u₁}</a> <span class=\"fn\">C</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">X</span> : <span class=\"fn\">C</span>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">P</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Functor/Basic.html#CategoryTheory.Functor\">Functor</a> <span class=\"fn\">C</span><a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Opposite.html#Opposite\">ᵒᵖ</a> <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">(Type</a> v₁)</span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">S</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Sites/Sieves.html#CategoryTheory.Sieve\">Sieve</a> <span class=\"fn\">X</span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Prop</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"This is an equivalent condition to be a sheaf, which is useful for the abstraction to local\noperators on elementary toposes. However this definition is defined only for sieves, not presieves.\nThe equivalence between this and `IsSheafFor` is given in `isSheafFor_iff_yonedaSheafCondition`.\nThis version is also useful to establish that being a sheaf is preserved under isomorphism of\npresheaves.\n\nSee the discussion before Equation (3) of [MM92], Chapter III, Section 4. See also C2.1.4 of\n[Elephant]. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Sites/IsSheafFor.html#CategoryTheory.Presieve.YonedaSheafCondition","kind":"def","line":466,"name":"CategoryTheory.Presieve.YonedaSheafCondition","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/087469e24922b85cb737497c74556c7dacc01f22/Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Sites/IsSheafFor.lean#L466-L476"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Sites/IsSheafFor.html#CategoryTheory.Presieve.IsSheafFor\"><span class=\"name\">CategoryTheory</span>.<span class=\"name\">Presieve</span>.<span class=\"name\">IsSheafFor</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">C</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u₁}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Category/Basic.html#CategoryTheory.Category\">Category.{v₁, u₁}</a> <span class=\"fn\">C</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">X</span> : <span class=\"fn\">C</span>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">P</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Functor/Basic.html#CategoryTheory.Functor\">Functor</a> <span class=\"fn\">C</span><a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Opposite.html#Opposite\">ᵒᵖ</a> <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">(Type</a> w)</span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">R</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Sites/Sieves.html#CategoryTheory.Presieve\">Presieve</a> <span class=\"fn\">X</span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Prop</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"We define `P` to be a sheaf for the presieve `R` if every compatible family has a unique\namalgamation.\n\nThis is the definition of a sheaf for the given presieve given in C2.1.2 of [Elephant], and\nhttps://ncatlab.org/nlab/show/sheaf#GeneralDefinitionInComponents.\nUsing `compatible_iff_sieveCompatible`,\nthis is equivalent to the definition of a sheaf in [MM92], Chapter III, Section 4.\n","docLink":"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Sites/IsSheafFor.html#CategoryTheory.Presieve.IsSheafFor","kind":"def","line":455,"name":"CategoryTheory.Presieve.IsSheafFor","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/087469e24922b85cb737497c74556c7dacc01f22/Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Sites/IsSheafFor.lean#L455-L464"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Sites/IsSheafFor.html#CategoryTheory.Presieve.isSeparatedFor_top\"><span class=\"name\">CategoryTheory</span>.<span class=\"name\">Presieve</span>.<span class=\"name\">isSeparatedFor_top</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">C</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u₁}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Category/Basic.html#CategoryTheory.Category\">Category.{v₁, u₁}</a> <span class=\"fn\">C</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">X</span> : <span class=\"fn\">C</span>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">P</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Functor/Basic.html#CategoryTheory.Functor\">Functor</a> <span class=\"fn\">C</span><a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Opposite.html#Opposite\">ᵒᵖ</a> <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">(Type</a> w)</span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Sites/IsSheafFor.html#CategoryTheory.Presieve.IsSeparatedFor\">IsSeparatedFor</a> <span class=\"fn\">P</span> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Order/Notation.html#Top.top\">⊤</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"","docLink":"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Sites/IsSheafFor.html#CategoryTheory.Presieve.isSeparatedFor_top","kind":"theorem","line":448,"name":"CategoryTheory.Presieve.isSeparatedFor_top","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/087469e24922b85cb737497c74556c7dacc01f22/Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Sites/IsSheafFor.lean#L448-L453"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Sites/IsSheafFor.html#CategoryTheory.Presieve.isSeparatedFor_iff_generate\"><span class=\"name\">CategoryTheory</span>.<span class=\"name\">Presieve</span>.<span class=\"name\">isSeparatedFor_iff_generate</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">C</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u₁}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Category/Basic.html#CategoryTheory.Category\">Category.{v₁, u₁}</a> <span class=\"fn\">C</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">P</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Functor/Basic.html#CategoryTheory.Functor\">Functor</a> <span class=\"fn\">C</span><a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Opposite.html#Opposite\">ᵒᵖ</a> <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">(Type</a> w)</span>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">X</span> : <span class=\"fn\">C</span>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">R</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Sites/Sieves.html#CategoryTheory.Presieve\">Presieve</a> <span class=