.<a href=\"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Sites/Sieves.html#CategoryTheory.Sieve.arrows\">arrows</a></span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">x</span>.<a href=\"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Sites/IsSheafFor.html#CategoryTheory.Presieve.FamilyOfElements.Compatible\">Compatible</a></span> <a href=\"./Init/Core.html#Iff\">↔</a> <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">x</span>.<a href=\"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Sites/IsSheafFor.html#CategoryTheory.Presieve.FamilyOfElements.SieveCompatible\">SieveCompatible</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"","docLink":"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Sites/IsSheafFor.html#CategoryTheory.Presieve.compatible_iff_sieveCompatible","kind":"theorem","line":241,"name":"CategoryTheory.Presieve.compatible_iff_sieveCompatible","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/087469e24922b85cb737497c74556c7dacc01f22/Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Sites/IsSheafFor.lean#L241-L248"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Sites/IsSheafFor.html#CategoryTheory.Presieve.FamilyOfElements.SieveCompatible\"><span class=\"name\">CategoryTheory</span>.<span class=\"name\">Presieve</span>.<span class=\"name\">FamilyOfElements</span>.<span class=\"name\">SieveCompatible</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">C</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u₁}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Category/Basic.html#CategoryTheory.Category\">Category.{v₁, u₁}</a> <span class=\"fn\">C</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">P</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Functor/Basic.html#CategoryTheory.Functor\">Functor</a> <span class=\"fn\">C</span><a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Opposite.html#Opposite\">ᵒᵖ</a> <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">(Type</a> w)</span>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">X</span> : <span class=\"fn\">C</span>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">S</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Sites/Sieves.html#CategoryTheory.Sieve\">Sieve</a> <span class=\"fn\">X</span></span>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">x</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Sites/IsSheafFor.html#CategoryTheory.Presieve.FamilyOfElements\">FamilyOfElements</a> <span class=\"fn\">P</span> <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">S</span>.<a href=\"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Sites/Sieves.html#CategoryTheory.Sieve.arrows\">arrows</a></span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Prop</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"If the arrow set for a family of elements is actually a sieve (i.e. it is downward closed) then the\nconsistency condition can be simplified.\nThis is an equivalent condition, see `compatible_iff_sieveCompatible`.\n\nThis is the notion of \"matching\" given for families on sieves given in [MM92], Chapter III,\nSection 4, Equation 1, and nlab: https://ncatlab.org/nlab/show/matching+family.\nSee also the discussion before Lemma C2.1.4 of [Elephant].\n","docLink":"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Sites/IsSheafFor.html#CategoryTheory.Presieve.FamilyOfElements.SieveCompatible","kind":"def","line":229,"name":"CategoryTheory.Presieve.FamilyOfElements.SieveCompatible","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/087469e24922b85cb737497c74556c7dacc01f22/Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Sites/IsSheafFor.lean#L229-L239"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Sites/IsSheafFor.html#CategoryTheory.Presieve.restrict_extend\"><span class=\"name\">CategoryTheory</span>.<span class=\"name\">Presieve</span>.<span class=\"name\">restrict_extend</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">C</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u₁}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Category/Basic.html#CategoryTheory.Category\">Category.{v₁, u₁}</a> <span class=\"fn\">C</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">P</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Functor/Basic.html#CategoryTheory.Functor\">Functor</a> <span class=\"fn\">C</span><a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Opposite.html#Opposite\">ᵒᵖ</a> <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">(Type</a> w)</span>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">X</span> : <span class=\"fn\">C</span>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">R</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Sites/Sieves.html#CategoryTheory.Presieve\">Presieve</a> <span class=\"fn\">X</span></span>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">x</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Sites/IsSheafFor.html#CategoryTheory.Presieve.FamilyOfElements\">FamilyOfElements</a> <span class=\"fn\">P</span> <span class=\"fn\">R</span></span>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<spa