unctor</a> <span class=\"fn\">C</span><a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Opposite.html#Opposite\">ᵒᵖ</a> <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">(Type</a> w)</span>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">X</span> : <span class=\"fn\">C</span>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Inhabited\">Inhabited</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Sites/IsSheafFor.html#CategoryTheory.Presieve.FamilyOfElements\">FamilyOfElements</a> <span class=\"fn\">P</span> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Order/Notation.html#Bot.bot\">⊥</a>)</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"","docLink":"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Sites/IsSheafFor.html#CategoryTheory.Presieve.instInhabitedFamilyOfElementsBot","kind":"instance","line":96,"name":"CategoryTheory.Presieve.instInhabitedFamilyOfElementsBot","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/087469e24922b85cb737497c74556c7dacc01f22/Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Sites/IsSheafFor.lean#L96-L97"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Sites/IsSheafFor.html#CategoryTheory.Presieve.FamilyOfElements\"><span class=\"name\">CategoryTheory</span>.<span class=\"name\">Presieve</span>.<span class=\"name\">FamilyOfElements</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">C</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u₁}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Category/Basic.html#CategoryTheory.Category\">Category.{v₁, u₁}</a> <span class=\"fn\">C</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">X</span> : <span class=\"fn\">C</span>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">P</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Functor/Basic.html#CategoryTheory.Functor\">Functor</a> <span class=\"fn\">C</span><a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Opposite.html#Opposite\">ᵒᵖ</a> <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">(Type</a> w)</span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">R</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Sites/Sieves.html#CategoryTheory.Presieve\">Presieve</a> <span class=\"fn\">X</span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> (max (max u₁ w) v₁)</div></div>","info":{"doc":"A family of elements for a presheaf `P` given a collection of arrows `R` with fixed codomain `X`\nconsists of an element of `P Y` for every `f : Y ⟶ X` in `R`.\nA presheaf is a sheaf (resp, separated) if every *compatible* family of elements has exactly one\n(resp, at most one) amalgamation.\n\nThis data is referred to as a `family` in [MM92], Chapter III, Section 4. It is also a concrete\nversion of the elements of the middle object in the Stacks entry which is\nmore useful for direct calculations. It is also used implicitly in Definition C2.1.2 in [Elephant].\n","docLink":"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Sites/IsSheafFor.html#CategoryTheory.Presieve.FamilyOfElements","kind":"def","line":83,"name":"CategoryTheory.Presieve.FamilyOfElements","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/087469e24922b85cb737497c74556c7dacc01f22/Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Sites/IsSheafFor.lean#L83-L94"}}],"imports":["Init","Mathlib.CategoryTheory.Sites.Sieves"],"instances":[{"className":"Inhabited","name":"CategoryTheory.Presieve.instInhabitedFamilyOfElementsBot","typeNames":["CategoryTheory.Presieve.FamilyOfElements"]}],"name":"Mathlib.CategoryTheory.Sites.IsSheafFor"}